\par
The PicoGame Mini (PGM) is a "cut down" version of the PicoGAME, having a single controller port which is identical to Port A of that system. It doesn't include the communications facilities or the LED indicator and is less versatile in other respects, but is appreciably smaller.\par
\par
Like its predecessor, it supports VGA output and a 5V PS/2 keyboard.  It also uses the PicoMite VGA version of MMBasic, developed by Geoff Graham and Peter Mather.\par
\par
The controller port is connected as follows:\par

